Brief Backgd

We are Performing this project to predict the way with which participants perform a barbell lift. Now a days we have the technology like Fitbit, Nike fuelband to collect data about a persons activities. The data used here is from: http://groupware.les.inf.puc-rio.br/har

We use various training and test sets from the sources online.

library(caret)
#usingcaret
setwd("C:/Users/MAHE/Documents")
#setingpath
#gtnurls
exeURL <- "http://d396qusza40orc.cloudfront.net/predmachlearn/pml-training.csv"
#gtnurlss
exetURL <- "http://d396qusza40orc.cloudfront.net/predmachlearn/pml-testing.csv"
#trngtransfer
trining <- read.csv(url(exeURL))
#tstng_trnfr
tstingg <- read.csv(url(exetURL))
label<- createDataPartition(trining$classe, p = 0.7, list = FALSE)
trinbb <- trining[label, ]
tstbbb <- trining[-label, ]

There are a lot of variables in the data set so we try to reduce them with the help of the below given chunk. Alot of these variables are not needed so we just get rid of them. The main goal of this stage is to reduce the data set by gettinig rid of some unwanted datas.

NnZro <- nearZeroVar(trinbb)
#varzero
trinbb <- trinbb[ ,-NnZro]
#trnngset
tstbbb <- tstbbb[ ,-NnZro]
#label_usntr
label<- apply(trinbb, 2, function(x) mean(is.na(x))) > 0.95
#bhbhb
trinbb <- trinbb[, -which(label, label== FALSE)]
tstbbb <- tstbbb[, -which(label, label == FALSE)]
trinbb <- trinbb[ , -(1:5)]
tstbbb <- tstbbb[ , -(1:5)]

third modell of gbm

#trying gbm method
library(caret)
#libcaret
set.seed(13908)
#cntrl_put
control <- trainControl(method = "repeatedcv", number = 5, repeats = 1, verboseIter = FALSE)
#modelled
modelGBbbm <- train(classe ~ ., data = trinbb, trControl = control, method = "gbm", verbose = FALSE)
modelGBbbm$finalModel
## A gradient boosted model with multinomial loss function.
## 150 iterations were performed.
## There were 53 predictors of which 53 had non-zero influence.
#prditd_usgn
predictGBbbm <- predict(modelGBbbm, tstbbb)
confMatrGBbbm <- confusionMatrix(predictGBbbm, tstbbb$classe)
